# OMNI Agent Protocol — mcp-sql-rust

Skills: `omni-token-economy`, `omni-mcp-playbook`. Setup: `docs/OMNI_CURSOR_SETUP.md`.

## Session start (before edits)

1. `omni_session` → `{"action":"status"}`
2. Topic knowledge → `omni_knowledge` `{"action":"query","key":"<topic>"}`
   Keys: `sql-guard`, `columnar-format`, `rmcp-tools`, `sqlx-dual`, `token-efficiency`

## Tool ladder

| Need | First | Fallback |
|------|-------|----------|
| Structural / call-graph / impact | **`codegraph_explore`** | `codegraph_node`, `codegraph callers` |
| String / config grep | `omni_search` or Shell `rg` | **never** native Grep |
| Project conventions | `omni_knowledge` | `docs/*.md` |
| Before editing hot file | `omni_context` | `codegraph_node` |
| Truncated shell (`[OMNI: ...]`) | `omni_retrieve` | re-run with narrower scope |
| Loop >3x no progress | STOP → ask user | — |
| Permanent quirk | `omni_knowledge` commit | — |
| Token audit | `omni_budget` / `omni stats --detail` | — |

## Hot files (always `omni_context` or codegraph before edit)

- `src/server.rs`
- `src/guard/mod.rs`, `src/guard/classify.rs`
- `src/db/exec.rs`
- `src/config.rs`
- `src/tools/core.rs`

## Shell hygiene

- Prefer `omni exec -- cargo test` for noisy builds when available
- Cap reads: `Read` with `limit` ≤ 250
- `git diff` / `rg` are auto-distilled by OMNI hooks — trust the signal

## End of task

- Commit new facts: `omni_knowledge` `action=commit`
- Optional: `omni remember "..."` for durable notes
- Check savings: `omni stats --today` (no pipe)
